				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "#Best practices"
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-06-11T11:04:14.358522-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-06-11T11:04:48.827395-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "nGrlX4MOT0+zcpJMzifmzg=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "##Editing vs. building"
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-06-11T11:04:53.803353-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-06-15T06:30:00.772111-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "9FS06+jKQ3GCp9wW7oi2oQ=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "In general, it is better to structure your rules as editing operations instead of building entirely new source text. For example, consider these two different rules for rewriting `begin` and `end` in blocks to `{}` for Javascript. The first edits the original source by changing the tokens to curly brackets:\n{{gtExample:GtSmaCCTransformationExamples>>jsBeginEndTransformation|noCode|previewShow=gtSimpleEditorFor:|previewHeight=350}}\nThe second replaces the original source with a string built from the statements in the block:\n{{gtExample:GtSmaCCTransformationExamples>>jsCopyingBeginEndTransformation|noCode|previewShow=gtSimpleEditorFor:|previewHeight=500}}\nThe first version is better not only because it is faster, but also because it preserves most of the formatting of the original code. It also makes debugging easier, because each edit operation is tagged with the rule that performed it."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-06-11T11:31:05.807344-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-06-11T11:31:08.707076-05:00"
					}
				},
